org.apache.flex.compiler.tree.mxml

Interface IMXMLModelPropertyContainerNode

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IASNode, IMXMLNode, ISourceLocation
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IMXMLModelPropertyNode, IMXMLModelRootNode

    public interface IMXMLModelPropertyContainerNode
extends IMXMLNode
    This type of AST node represents tags inside an MXML <Model> tag that contain other tags.

    It is the superinterface for IMXMLModelRootNode and IMXMLModelPropertyNode.

      • getPropertyNames

        String[] getPropertyNames()
        The names of the properties to be set on this node.
        Returns:
        The names of the properties as an array of Strings. If this node has more than one child IMXMLModelPropertyNode with the same name, the property name appears only once in this array.

      • getPropertyNodes

        IMXMLModelPropertyNode[] getPropertyNodes(String propertyName)
        The child property nodes with a specified property name.
        Parameters:
        propertyName - A property name.
        Returns:
        An array of IMXMLModelPropertyNode objects. This will often be a single-element array, but there will be multiple elements if this node has more than one child IMXMLModelPropertyNode with the same name.

      • getIndex

        int getIndex()
        If this node has the same name as a sibling, then this field stores that it is the i'th one, in attribute-then-child-tag order. If it is the only one, its index is IMXMLModelPropertyContainerNode.NO_INDEX.
        Returns:
        The index as an int.
